    "Name": "Coriolis CRLS-386b",
    "Details": "The CRLS-386b is the SLDF Royal Division's take on the Coriolis, swapping the AC/20 for a Gauss Rifle on an Endo Steel frame to save weight. The LB-10X remains in the right arm while Medium Pulse Lasers and an ER Large Laser round out a well-balanced weapons suite. CASE protects both ammunition bays. Three jump jets keep the rear-arc ambush capability that defines the chassis, now backed by considerably more sophisticated firepower.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Accurate Weapon - AC</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.16</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limit: Right Lower</color>",
